      "id": "1507807238935417086",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-05-23T18:07:39.466+00:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Hi everyone.\nThis is my first public open-silicon review package, so I\u2019d really appreciate ASIC/PD feedback.\nI built a compact 3.3V-only GF180 I/O candidate library for wafer.space/open MPW experiments:\n- 160um pad depth\n- 100 signal pads\n- ~17.3mm\u00b2 usable core area\n- local DRC/LVS completed\n- LEF/CDL/SPICE/Liberty/IBIS generation\n- preliminary ngspice PVT/DC characterization\n- config/package generation flow included\nThe project was developed using an automated agent-in-the-loop exploration flow with manual review and verification.\nMain goal: reduce padframe overhead for small GF180 SoCs.\nAny comments on architecture, verification flow, pad strategy, or obvious mistakes would be greatly appreciated.\nhttps://github.com/Detronyx-labs/gf180_compact_3v3_io.git",
      "author": {
        "id": "510792389992906754",
        "name": "zhekar1998",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "Zhekar1998",
        "color": null,
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [],
        "avatarUrl": "2026-05_media/0-EB806.png"
      },
      "attachments": [],
